  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0bc1\u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0bca\u0b9f\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bbe\u0ba9 \u0b95\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bb3\u0bc8\u0b9a\u0bcd \u0b9a\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc8\u0ba4\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4 \u0ba4\u0bc0\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0bae\u0bbe\u0ba9\u0bae\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Resolution to amend the Ordinance relating to children",
      "author": "Vishnu",
      "body_lines": [
        "The government has decided to amend the Ordinance relating to children and juveniles and to introduce new legislation on child protection and justice.",
        "The United Nations Convention on the Rights of the Child defines a child as any child under the age of 18 years. Approval was given at the Cabinet meeting held on 16th September 2020 to amend the Ordinance relating to children and juveniles in accordance with the relevant Convention and its provisions.",
        "The Attorney General has approved the bill prepared by the Attorney General for the purpose. Accordingly, the Cabinet approved the proposal submitted by the Minister of Justice, Prisons Affairs and Constitutional Reforms to publish the Bill in the Gazette and then submit it to Parliament for approval.",
        "Meanwhile, a Cabinet meeting was held on 18 February 2015 to prepare a Bill relating to the Juvenile Justice (Judicial Protection) to enable the judiciary to exercise its jurisdiction to prosecute or prosecute a child in need of protection and insurance and to establish courts that would otherwise exercise judicial power over a child. Authorization granted.",
        "Further proposals have been examined and submitted by two special expert committees for the basic bill prepared by the Legislature.",
        "The Cabinet approved the proposal submitted by the Minister of Justice, Prisons Affairs and Constitutional Reforms to advise the legislator to prepare a final bill including the proposals in the Basic Bill which is currently being prepared."
      ],
